<title>NEW ZEALAND: NZ's Clear CEO Makin resigns.</title>
<headline>NZ's Clear CEO Makin resigns.</headline>
<dateline>WELLINGTON 1997-05-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>Clear Communications said on Wednesday it had accepted the resignation of its chief executive, Andrew Makin.  </p>
<p>Clear is owned in equal proportions by British Telecom, MCI Communications Corp, the New Zealand family-owned Todd Corporation and state-owned Television New Zealand.</p>
<p>Makin, CEO of the telephone company, said he was leaving for a lifestyle change.</p>
<p>He said he would stay in his job until a successor was appointed.</p>
<p>--Wellington Newsroom (64 4) 4734746</p>
